en_52314_0	The much-anticipated meeting between US President Donald Trump and North Korean leader Kim Jong-un will take place at a hotel on the Singaporean island of Sentosa, the White House has confirmed.
en_52314_1	The historic summit is scheduled to take place on 12th of this month, but many details are still unconfirmed.
en_52314_2	It will be the first meeting between a North Korean leader and a sitting US president.
en_52314_3	White House press secretary Sarah Sanders confirmed on Twitter that the summit would take place at the five-star Capella Hotel.
